legacy.full_text: Suzhou’s 4,000 year-old lacquerware is a cultural gem. As a decorative art that involves applying layers of sap from a lacquer tree, this cultural gem hit its peak 500 years ago during the Ming Dynasty. Today, visitors to Suzhou can enjoy its relics at museums. https://t.co/2r5I6RQrGy
